cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with object recognition and feature extraction from images, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves synthesising visual features for unseen classes, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of semantic attributes as an intermediate clue also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the benchmark datasets used in the experiments involve images and videos, indicating a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
